f=Governance/precedent/custom/case-law-method/SKILL.md · in=case-law-method reasoning discipline *using* precedent: given new case retrieved prior ruling, extract what prior ruling actually decided (its ratio rule drove outcome, opposed incidental commentary), test whether new case's material facts genuinely match, **apply distinguish explicitly** never silently. adapts common-law stare-decisis method internal governance rulings; involves real courts, legal research, legal advice. · p=Without method, precedent retrieval produces two failure modes: rulings get applied because they're superficially similar ("we approved spend like before" different facts), ignored because nobody articulates they don't bind. skill forces middle path: relevant precedent either applied rule stated, distinguished material difference named. Consistency cases match; documented reasons they don't. · wu=Triggers: "apply precedent," "how past ruling bear this," "are cases same," whenever `ruling-log` surfaced precedents live gate review board needs know what they require. · st:/ Protocol=`Extract the ratio from the prior ruling (the rule that decided it, not the commentary) \· -> Identify the prior case's material facts (the facts the ratio depended on) \· -> Compare the new case's facts: same in the ways that mattered? \· -> APPLY (facts match → same ruling follows, rule quoted) \· or DISTINGUISH (material difference named → precedent doesn't control)` · h3:Phase Extract Ratio=prior ruling's record (its `rationale` `cited` fields): state one sentence *rule* decided "spends above gate unvalidated revenue assumptions get CONDITIONAL, APPROVE" separated incidental observations didn't drive outcome. record's rationale missing thin extract ratio, say so: ruling without extractable reasoning weak precedent, usable history rule. · h3:Phase Material Facts=List facts prior case *that ratio depended on* (amount relative gate, what unvalidated, which article applied). Facts didn't matter outcome noise naming them material false matches happen. · h3:Phase 3 — Compare=material fact, new case same, different, unknown? Unknown facts get asked about, assumed match. · h3:Phase Apply Distinguish=**APPLY** material facts match: precedent's rule controls, new ruling follow it. Quote ratio prior ruling ID. Departing applied precedent **overrule** allowed, belongs `consistency-check`'s explicit distinguish-or-overrule protocol, never done silently here., **DISTINGUISH** material fact differs: name specifically ("prior case's spend one-time; one recurring, which changes runway math"), state precedent doesn't control *for reason*. distinction wouldn't changed prior outcome material don't manufacture distinctions escape inconvenient precedent. · h3:Phase 5 — Record=application/distinction goes new ruling's record (ruling-log schema, `rationale` field references precedent IDs), precedent chain stays traceable. · of=`## Precedent Application: [new case] vs [ruling ID] \·  \· **Ratio of prior ruling:** [one sentence, quoted basis] \· **Material facts (prior):** [list] \· ` · pr=**Ratio, vibes.** What ruling *decided* binds; what *mentioned* doesn't., **Material means outcome-changing.** distinction wouldn't flipped prior ruling distinction., **Explicit nothing.** surfaced precedent ends APPLY DISTINGUISH writing silence about known precedent failure skill exists prevent., **Thin precedent history, rule.** Rulings without captured rationale inform, don't control., **Not legal advice.** Internal governance reasoning only; real legal questions counsel (and jurisdiction compliance sentinel's domain). · f=precedents surfaced nothing apply; new ruling stands becomes tomorrow's precedent., Two precedents conflict surface `consistency-check` (that's latent contradiction log, territory)., prior record lacks rationale treat thin-precedent principle; flag ruling-log's "rationale captured" hygiene. · b:with Other precedent Skills=`ruling-log` finds precedents; skill reasons one precedent new case; `consistency-check` handles *conflict* cases proposed ruling contradicts applied precedent triggers distinguish-or-overrule protocol., Boundary board: skill tells board what precedent requires; board (and ultimately operator) still owns ruling. Precedent informs gate; doesn't replace it.